sing team concepts and techniques to accomplish departmental/plant objectives. You will assist and support maintenance programmes to ensure increased asset reliability. You will maintain and enforce effective financial and internal controls in order to achieve zero audit finding. You will be responsible for the full compliance with Government Regulations and Corporate Policies. You will be the Owner of Critical Task Management and the driver of the EHS Maturity Transformation journey for the Converting plant Skills/Experience: Minimum of a BTech in Production Management or Engineering, a BSc Degree preferably in Operations, Science or Engineering Post Graduate qualifications in Leadership or Business Administration are advantageous Minimum of 5 years plant and people leadership experience in a fast moving consumer goods (FMCG) environment is required, of which at least 3 years must be in a leadership role. Proven record of operational success or related business success. Sound management and leadership skills are essential and above average computer literacy is required. Knowledge of the OHSAct and an understanding of ISO systems would be advantageous Global VISA and Relocation Specifications: Primary Location South Africa- Enstra Additional Locations Worker Type Employee Worker Sub-Type Regular Time Type Full time Apply Now South Africa United StatesCanada ArgentinaAustraliaBelgiÃ«BrasilDeutschlandEspaÃ±aFranceIndiaIrelandItaliaMÃ©xicoNederlandÃsterreichPortugalSchweizSouth AfricaSverigeUnited KingdomÐ Ð¾ÑÑÐ¸Ñíêµ­ä¸­å½æ¥æ¬ Â© 2020 SH Inc. | Privacy | TermsÂ |Â Privacy Center"
